      • Airport

        public Airport(java.lang.String name,
               java.lang.String city,
               java.lang.String country,
               java.lang.String iata,
               java.lang.String icao,
               double latitude,
               double longitude,
               double altitude,
               java.lang.String timeZone,
               java.lang.String dst,
               java.lang.String timeZoneDatabase,
               int numRoutes)
        Creates a new airport object, specifying the number of routes.
        Parameters:
        name - name of airport
        city - main city served by airport
        country - country or territory where airport is located
        iata - 3-letter IATA/FAA (International Air Travel Association / Federal Aviation Authority [for US airports]) code
        icao - 4-letter ICAO (International Civil Aviation Organization) code
        latitude - decimal degrees, usually to six significant digits. Negative is South, positive is North.
        longitude - decimal degrees, usually to six significant digits. Negative is West, positive is East.
        altitude - height, in feet.
        timeZone - hours offset from UTC
        dst - daylight savings time
        timeZoneDatabase - timezone in "tz" (Olson) format
        numRoutes - number of routes
